According to a new report from Intel Market Research, global Hybrid Articulated Boom Lifts market was valued at USD 444 million in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 561 million by 2034, exhibiting a robust CAGR of 3.5% during the forecast period (2025–2034). This growth is propelled by stricter emissions regulations, rising construction activity worldwide, and the growing demand for versatile equipment that can operate safely in confined spaces.

The hybrid articulated boom lift is an aerial work equipment that combines a diesel engine with an electric drive system. This dual‑power architecture leverages the high torque of diesel for demanding outdoor tasks while using electric propulsion for quiet, zero‑emission operation indoors or in emission‑restricted zones, delivering both productivity and sustainability.

